painful childhood in a new memoir.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   REFUGEES-FILMS (Undated) _ Filmaid International, organized in
just eight weeks, traveled last year to five refugee camps in
Macedonia and assembled an open-air movie house to screen movies
like ``Titanic,'' ``Mrs. Doubtfire'' and ``E.T.'' Now it is an
official project of the International Rescue Committee, which along
with the U.N. high commissioner for refugees helped support the
project. But the initial funds came from a source not exactly famed
for its global philanthropy: Hollywood. By Jesse McKinley.
</P>
<P>
   BOORSTIN-TV (Undated) _ A Critic's Notebook: Way back in 1961
Daniel Boorstin predicted such television shows as ``Survivors''
and ``Big Brother.'' By Waltert Goodman.
