   MEXICO-ELECTION _ MEXICO CITY _ President-election Vicente Fox
meets with the foreign press to begin laying out how he will build
a transitional government after ending the 71-year-old reign of the
ruling Institutional Revolutionary Party, or PRI. As ballots
continue to be counted from Sunday's election, it appears the PRI
also lost control of its majority in the Senate and that it will no
longer be the largest political force in the House. (Ferriss, Cox
News Service).
