   SCHUETT-COLUMN05 - GIBSONBURG, Ohio - For one brief and shining
Camelot moment, before the numbness of sleep has washed from my
awareness, all's right in a perfect world. ``Mee-owww,'' a small
voice calls from the doorway to my porch. I roll over for a look.
Biddy, my 11-year-old Siamese sits daintily on the threshold
awaiting our morning chat - lopsided though it may be. I tell her
I'll be there in a minute and invite her into the hammock for a
snuggle. She refuses and chatters on.(Schuett, Cox News Service)
MOVED MONDAY.
