   BUSINESSMONEYTALK _ Millions of Americans still choose to lease
their new cars. Why would that many people want to make payments on
a big-ticket item, one they will use every day, when they know that
they will never own it? The answer is money. The upfront cost is
usually cheaper, and monthly payments can be a lot less. (Ezell,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED MONDAY.
