enrolled in summer school this season, as districts throughout the
country require or strongly encourage younger and younger students
to attend classes to shore up basic reading and mathematical
skills. Educational experts believe summer school helps address the
yawning academic gaps between poor, minority students and white
middle-class ones, by slowing the ``summer slide,'' in which
children forget study skills and discipline habits. But many are
worried that the mushrooming programs will simply frustrate
struggling students with endless drills for high-stakes exams. By
Jodi Wilgoren.
