<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, June 27
about the evolving design of the Columbus Center project on
Columbus Circle omitted the name of one of the architectural firms
involved. The residential portion of Columbus Center is being
designed by Ismael Levya Architects.
</P>
