<P>
   BC-OBIT-MAGENER-NYT (moved on Sunday, July 2)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service correction sent yesterday of the
date of death in an obituary on Monday of a German businessman who
escaped from a British internment camp in World War II misspelled
the man's surname. He was Rolf Magener, not Mageren.  &QL;
