<HEADLINE>
MASON ARRESTED IN NEW ORLEANS 
</HEADLINE>
   By LENA WILLIAMS   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Anthony Mason, the former Knick who now plays for the Charlotte
Hornets, was arrested on Monday night in New Orleans and charged
with inciting a riot, assaulting a police officer and resisting
arrest, the police said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   The incident occurred shortly after 9 p.m. Monday when New
Orleans police officers responded to an argument between two groups
of men in the French Quarter. The police said that when officers
tried to separate the men, Mason struck one of the officers without
provocation.
</P>
<P>
   The police said the 6-foot-7, 270-pound Mason was sprayed with
pepper spray after he resisted officers' attempts to arrest him.
They said Mason managed to flee but was caught a short distance
from the scene. After he was handcuffed, the police said, Mason
began to incite a crowd that had gathered, yelling to them to help
him escape.
</P>
<P>
   It was the latest in a string of run-ins the 33-year-old Mason,
a native of Queens, has had with the police, dating back to 1989.
</P>
</TEXT>
